CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "Holiday House Glistens With D.I.'s Style Show and Dance Benefit for MENDS, the National Foundation for Neuromuscular Diseases, Inc."
TitMainTitle: Gloria Golden Grate and Birdie Dunlap, standing with two men, pulling objects out of two trunks on metal stands, standing in front of musicians and shirred satin curtain with pleated fabric valance in the Holiday House for D. I. Club's "Melody in Fashions" benefit for MENDS
